  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth version`\r\n\r\n```\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.10.1-stable\r\nGit Commit: c2d2f4ed8f232bb11663a1b01a2e578aa22f24bd\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nGo Version: go1.16\r\nOperating System: linux\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=go\r\n```\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\n\r\n```\r\nDistributor ID: Debian\r\nDescription:    Debian GNU/Linux 10 (buster)\r\nRelease:        10\r\nCodename:       buster\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nSyncing fast till currentBlock equals highestBlock.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nSyncing slow till about 35% and then the db reset leaving me with a currentlbock of 0.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nMy service file is looking like followed:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[Unit]\r\nDescription=The Ethereum Blockchain Command Line Interface\r\nDocumentation=man:geth(1)\r\nRequires=network.target\r\n\r\n[Service]\r\nType=forking\r\nUser=%I\r\nExecStart=/usr/bin/geth --syncmode fast --cache=4096 --mine --miner.threads=15 --miner.etherbase 0x0467f8979845f87614d36abe7de8fbb1968f919f\r\nRestart=on-failure\r\n\r\n[Install]\r\nWantedBy=multi-user.target\r\n```\r\n\r\nI have enabled it over systemctl and it is starting on boot. On my firewall I have port 30303 forwarded.\r\n\r\nBeen stuck on this now for about five days and haven't gotten one successful sync so far. I am using M.2 SSDs and there is more than enough space on them (500GB+).\r\n",
